                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ARTICLE 6</b></td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>SECURITY DEPOSIT AND REFUND THEREOF</b>  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>6.1</b>	Prior to the disbursement of the Loan Amount as sanctioned by KFI, the Borrower shall pay to KFI, the sum mentioned in Schedule-I/Sanction Letter hereunder, as and by way of Security Deposit to ensure due compliance by the Borrower with the terms and conditions of this Agreement including the assurance by Borrower of terminal value of the Hypothecated Assets as specified from time to time. The said deposit shall be refundable/adjusted as per the Security Deposit Receipt, (which the parties agree has been mutually negotiated and settled), provided that:</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>i.</b>	Borrower is not in default under any of the terms and conditions of this Agreement.</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ii.</b>	KFI shall, at its sole discretion, be entitled to, appropriate any amount or amounts from time to time, without any notice to the Borrower, out of such security deposit along with interest thereon, if any to be utilized for payment of any amount that might have fallen due to KFI, and to that extent, the Security Deposit shall be deemed to have reduced/debited.</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iii.</b>	KFI may require the Borrower by notice to forthwith make good any reduction/deficit in the security deposit as and when the same is in deficit and deemed necessary by KFI. Any such reduction shall, on date of such notification by KFI, be deemed to be the amount due and payable by the Borrowerunder the terms of this Agreement. The Borrower hereby confers an unconditional Lien upon KFI in respect of the security deposit and interest accruing thereon and grants to KFI an unconditional right to adjust these monies to first set off costs incurred in relation to enforcement of this Agreement and then set off the delayed payment charges arising out of late remittance of installment due under this Agreement and finally to set off installment due and payable in the inverse order of maturity. From the amount to be refunded, KFI shall be entitled to make the following deductions:</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>a.</b>	All sums that have remained unpaid by the Borrower; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>b.</b>	An estimated amount on account of sums payable by the Borrower, the exact amount of which, is not ascertainable at the time of such refund; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>c.</b>	Insurance premiums remaining unpaid by the Borrower; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>d.</b>	Where, in view of the continuing indemnities provided by the Borrower hereto or for any other reason, it is likely that any liability on the Borrower shall arise in future, KFI may retain such part of the deposit along with interest thereon, if any, as it deems fit and necessary to make good such liability. The part so retained shall be adjustable against the liability for which it was retained, or any other liability of the Borrower to the extent the same remains unsatisfied, and the balance shall be refundable to the Borrower after all such apprehended liabilities have been fully satisfied; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>6.2</b>	Where the whole or any part of the Security Deposit is refunded or adjusted at any time before the expiry of the full term of loan under this Agreement, such amount as refunded or adjusted shall be discounted, from the time of such refund or adjustment to the expiry of the term of loan under this Agreement, at the discounting rate as applicable. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ARTICLE 7</b></td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>SECURITY </b></td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>7.1</b>	As security for the due repayment, discharge and redemption of the Loan Amount and with the intent to secure the Loan Amount, the Borrower will create such security as more particularly described in Schedule I hereunder for repayment of the Loan Amount alongwith the agreed interest and other charge/s, expense/s etc., and for the creation of such security, the Borrower has agreed to execute the following documents in favor of KFI: </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");

                //sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                //sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'>&nbsp;</td>");
                //sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                //sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                //sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'>&nbsp;</td>");
                //sb.Append(@"</tr>");

                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>i.</b>	Demand Promissory Note</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ii.</b>	Agreement of Hypothecation of Assets:The Borrower/Guarantor as the case may be has entered /shall also execute a separate Agreement of Hypothecation to hypothecate the Asset(s) (i.e. the ones to be purchased or the ones already purchased) in favor of KFI. The Borrower/Guarantor has executed and/or undertaken to execute a Power of Attorney in favor of  KFI on any date prior to the date of disbursement of the Loan Amount to give effect to the terms of the this Agreement. The said Hypothecation Agreement and the Power of Attorney shall form part and parcel of this Agreement and shall be read in consonance with the terms of this Agreement. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iii.</b>	Guarantee Deeds:At the instance of Borrower, certain Guarantor/s and / or Surety/ies have executed and/or have undertaken to execute the Guarantee Deed/s and thereby agreed and undertaken to repay the dues of KFI in case of default in payment by the Borrower. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iv.</b>	Post Dated cheques- As mentioned in Schedule II hereto. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>7.2</b>	The Borrower shall furnish to KFI all such statements and returns of the cost and market value of securities and a full description thereof and produce such evidence in support thereof as KFI may from time to time require and shall at all times during continuance of this Agreement keep and maintain such margin of the security as may be required by KFI from time to time. If and so often as the margin shall fail to be maintained then the Borrower shall forthwith (as KFI may require) either hypothecate to KFI further Assets or other securities of sufficient value, approved by KFI to make up the deficiency or shall reduce the amount for the time being due to KFI by a cash payment so as to maintain the said margin. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>7.3</b>	Additional Security: The Borrower undertakes to create from time to time such additional Security in favor of KFI as security for the repayment/payment of the Borrower’s Dues or/and Obligations as KFI may require and in such manner as the KFI may require and to execute and/or furnish to KFI such guarantee(s) and other documents and writings as KFI may require. The Borrower undertakes to obtain from time to time such additional Guarantees from the Guarantors as KFI may require in favor of KFI.  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>7.4</b>	Continuing Security:The Security given under this Agreement or under any document in terms of this Agreement or otherwise at any time given to KFI, shall be and remain a continuing security to KFI and accordingly shall:  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>i.</b>	be binding on the Borrower/Guarantor or any other person who has provided Security under this Agreement</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ii.</b>	shall extend to cover the Borrower’s Dues hereunder or otherwise </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iii.</b>	shall not be discharged by any immediate payment by the Borrower or any settlement of accounts between the Borrower and KFI.  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iv.</b>	shall be in addition to and not in substitution or derogation of any other security which KFI may at any time hold in respect of the Borrower’s Dues/obligations hereunder</td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>v.</b>	shall be a Security for all amounts due and payable by the Borrower for all sums due by the Borrower to KFI whether under this Agreement or otherwise. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>7.5</b>	The Security created under this Agreement shall not be released till such time that the Borrower owes to KFI any amount whatsoever under any other facility availed by the Borrower from KFI from time to time. KFI shall be entitled to treat the Security created under this Agreement as continuing security for any/all amounts that are/shall become due in respect of this Facility/Facilities or any other facilities availed by the Borrower from KFI.  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ARTICLE 8</b>  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>EVENTS OF DEFAULT AND CONSEQUENCES THEREOF</b>  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>8.1</b> 	If the Borrower shall fail to carry out and perform any of the obligations under this Agreement or commit breach of any of the terms hereof or of the Sanction Letter Transaction Documents or of the terms of the Request which forms the basis of this Agreement, or if any of the representations, warranties, assurances, statements and particulars contained in the Request being found in KFI’s opinion (which shall be conclusive and binding on the Borrower) to be incorrect, or if after execution hereof, any circumstance shall occur which in the sole judgment of KFI is prejudicial to or imperils or is likely to prejudice or imperil this Facilities and the securities created thereunder, then KFI shall, if it thinks fit, be entitled at the risk and expense of the Borrower after giving notice at any time or time after such occurrence and in its sole judgment to refuse to grant the said Facilities or any part thereof which may remain to be disbursed or to recall the said Facilities and/or to enforce the security that may be/is required to be created thereunder. On the question whether any of the events, matters or circumstances mentioned above have or has occurred, the opinion of KFI shall be final, conclusive and binding on the Borrower, both in and out of court/ judicial/ quasi-judicial authority. It shall not be open to the Borrower at any stage to question the decision of KFI to refuse to grant the said Facilities or any part thereof which may remain to be disbursed or to recall the said Facilities and/or to enforce the security created thereunder. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>8.2</b>	It is agreed between the parties, that any of the following events shall be considered to be an Event of Default under the terms of this Agreement:  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>i.</b>	In event the Borrower(s) fails to repay the Loan Amount or any fee, charges, costs, etc. in a manner herein contained and/or any one installment or any other amount due hereunder remains unpaid on the date on which it is so due; or </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ii.</b>	In event of the death/lunacy of the Borrower(s) or the Guarantor(s) (in case of either of them being an individual and in case more than one, any one of them) </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iii.</b>	In event the Borrower entering in any arrangement or composition with the Borrower’s creditors or committing any act of insolvency or being declared insolvent; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>iv.</b>	In event the Borrower committing any act the consequences of which may lead to winding up of the Borrower’s business; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>v.</b>	Execution or distress or other processes being enforced or levied upon or against the whole or any part of the Hypothecated Asset(s) or the Borrower’s property whether secured or not to KFI;  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>vi.</b>	In  event the Borrower goes into liquidation whether at its own instance or otherwise;  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>vii.</b>	In event a Receiver is appointed in respect of the whole or part of the property of the Borrower including the Hypothecated Assets; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>viii.</b>	In event the Borrower voluntarily or involuntarily ceases or threatens to cease to carry on business; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>ix.</b>	In event the Borrower fails to insure the Hypothecated Assets as stipulated in Article 10 hereunder;   </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>x.</b>	In event, any representation or statement made herein by the Borrower being found to be incorrect;   </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xi.</b>	In event  the Borrower(s) or Guarantor(s) (in case of either of them being a corporation or a partnership firm) takes any action or causes to take such action/steps or other steps are taken or legal proceedings are initiated for winding up, dissolution or reorganization or for the appointment of a receiver, trustee or similar officer on its assets, particularly on the Hypothecated Asset(s); or  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xii.</b>	In event  the Borrower(s) sells, pledges, mortgages, encumbers,  transfers and/or creates any third party rights over the Hypothecated Asset(s) in any manner whatsoever without the express consent in writing of KFI or the Hypothecated Asset(s) are confiscated, attached, taken into custody by any authority or subject to an execution proceeding; or  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xiii.</b> In event any such circumstance arises which in the opinion of KFI is likely to prejudice or endanger the Hypothecated Asset(s);  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xiv.</b>	the occurrence of any event or condition which, in the  KFI’s opinion, constitutes or could constitute a Material Adverse Effect; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xv.</b>	In event the Borrower(s) commits breach of any of the terms, covenants, representations, warranties and conditions herein contained and/or in the security documents and any other term or condition relating to advance or has made any misrepresentations to KFI; or  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xvi.</b>	 In event the Borrower pays off the unsecured loans and/or withdraws monies from the capital / reserves and surplus/current accounts without the prior written permission of KFI; or  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xvii.</b>	In event the Borrower/Guarantor utilizes the Hypothecated Asset(s) for any other purpose other than the purpose for which the Loan Amount has been sanctioned and for the purpose as provided in this  Agreement; </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xviii.</b>	In event there is any delay, deferment and/or alteration/modification in the repayment/amortization schedule;  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xix.</b>	In event the Borrower fails to submit the “Original for Buyer” Tax Invoice/document of title pertaining to the Hypothecated Assets/Machineries;  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>xx.</b>	And, if there exists any other circumstance which in the sole opinion of KFI jeopardizes KFI’s rights and interest under the terms and conditions of this Agreement. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>8.3	Consequences in case of Event of Default by the Borrower and Repossession of the Hypothecated Assets:</b> Without prejudice to its rights under this Agreement and/or under law for the time being in force, upon the occurrence of any/all of the Events of Default by the Borrower/Guarantor, KFI may at its option , without the specific intervention of a court or any court order, by written notices to the Borrower(s) and the Guarantor(s) declare the loan to be immediately due and payable, whereupon the same shall become payable together with accrued interest thereon and any other sums then owed by the Borrower(s) herein immediately upon being called upon by KFI; or </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                //sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                //sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'>&nbsp;  </td>");
                //sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>8.4</b>	In the aforesaid Events of Default, the Borrower(s) shall not prevent or obstruct KFI from taking the possession of the Hypothecated Asset(s) and/or mortgaged assets if any and shall forthwith upon being called to do so, handover the possession of the Hypothecated and/or mortgaged assets to the representatives of KFI within 10 days from the date of notice for taking possession of the Hypothecated Assets. For this purpose KFI’s authorized representatives, servants, officers and agents will have unrestricted right of entry in any premises of the Borrower(s) or rented premises acquired by Borrower as informed to KFI or any place where the Hypothecated Asset(s) is/are stationed and shall be entitled to repossession of the asset(s). During the period of notice for taking possession, the Borrower undertakes to take reasonable and adequate care of the Hypothecated Asset(s).  </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
                sb.AppendFormat(@"<td width='100%' align='justify' style='font-family:Garamond,Geneva, sans-serif; font-size:16px; line-height:16px;'><b>8.5</b>	For the aforesaid purpose, it shall be justified that KFI, to forthwith or at any time without notice to the Borrower(s), to enter upon the premises which may be owned or leased by the Borrower from a third party, where the Hypothecated Asset(s) shall be lying or kept, and to take possession or recover and receive the same and if necessary to break open any such place. The Borrower(s) shall be liable to pay any transportation cost and other such expenses incurred by KFI for effecting the repossession of the Hypothecated Assets and for its safe keeping etc. The Borrower undertakes to cooperate with KFI at all such times. </td>");
                sb.Append(@"</tr>");
                sb.Append(@"<tr>");
